subSubSection.paragraph: Distribution. Australia ( Tasmania , South Australia , Western Australia , New South Wales ).

Variation. Body length 5.29–7.42 mm ; LFW 3.10–4.53 mm ; mandible ranging in color from castaneous to dark castaneous almost black; clypeus angulate to subangulate, but slightly medially emarginated; Rs b of forewing almost straight; discal carina of propodeal disc short (shorter than half length of disc) to long (longer than half length of disc).

Remarks. This species was originally describeb by Dodd (1916) . However, this species was redescribed and illustrated by Terayama (2004) . He also broadend the known distribution considerably, since the species was hitherto known only from the holotype . Here, we got 53 specimens .
